60.1	Stollen	Stollen	A Stollen is a fruit cake containing dried fruit and covered with sugar, powdered sugar or icing sugar. The cake is usually made with chopped candied fruit and/or dried fruit, nuts and spices. Stollen is a traditional German cake, usually eaten during the Christmas season, when called Weihnachtsstollen or Christstollen. A similar cake, found in Dutch cuisine, is called a Kerststol in Dutch, whilst in Italian cuisine the panettone also shows a likeness.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/44/Stollen-Dresdner_Christstollen.jpg/270px-Stollen-Dresdner_Christstollen.jpg
